data.name: label12.ToolTip
data.value: This directory should be the location of your GameUserSettings.ini and Engine.ini file for Dead By Daylight. Eg. C:\Users\YOURPCNAMEHERE\AppData\Local\DeadByDaylight\Saved\Config\WindowsNoEditor

data.name: FullScreenOn.ToolTip
data.value: Runs Dead By Daylight in proper FullScreen, rather than borderless windowed which it currently runs in. This is helpful for those who want to use stretched resolution and not have a massive monitor reload each time you swap tabs.

data.name: label10.ToolTip
data.value: This shows the current Game Settings, if nothing is displayed here, enter your DBD's WindowsNoEditorDirectory into the text box at the bottom and hit "Submit Directory", it should then work, if not, dm me.

data.name: label11.ToolTip
data.value: This shows the current Engine Settings, if nothing is displayed here, enter your DBD's WindowsNoEditorDirectory into the text box at the bottom and hit "Submit Directory", it should then work, if not, dm me.

data.name: UltraGraphics.ToolTip
data.value: This mode allows you to edit each setting individually, without the bounds that DBD natively supports, for example, normally TextureQuality is 3 at max, but by enabling Ultra Graphics mode, this allows you to exceed this value up to 5 at great performance cost.

data.name: NormalEditor.ToolTip
data.value: This mode allows you to edit each setting individually, within the bounds that DBD natively supports, for example, normally AnimationQuality is 5 at max, but basically everything else only goes to 3, enabling Ultra Graphics mode, allows you to exceed this at great performance cost.

data.name: label15.ToolTip
data.value: Please dont spam me with stupid stuff, if you have found a genuine issue or have valuable suggestions/feedback, please dm me. I may not always respond/ respond right away. I have a life, enjoy the tool.

data.name: ReadOnlyOff.ToolTip
data.value: Clicking this will make it so DBD is now able to edit your settings, this must be done AFTER you have made changes in the editor, then make the changes ingame. Using this tool sets your settings files to readonly so that DBD cannot change them back, but it also means, for example, changing audio levels will NOT save once using this tool.
